        "inline_data": null,
        "text": "# \ud83d\udfe2 HEARTBEAT_WAKEUP\nYou have been routed ONE isolated task. \n*Task ID*: EPIC-DFP-MOD-data-store\n*Module*: data-store\n*Workdir*: /home/ienliven/Projects/sdlc-factory/workspace/EPIC-DFP-MOD-data-store\n*Phase*: TEST_DESIGN\n\n## SYSTEM CONTEXT\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"success\",\n  \"module_id\": \"data-store\",\n  \"regression_context\": \"No active regression reported.\",\n  \"structural_context\": \"## > BEGIN_ENVIRONMENT\\n- **Stack**: Docker Compose (React/Vite/Nginx, Python/FastAPI, PostgreSQL)\\n- **Entry_Point**: `http://localhost:8000` (UI) and `http://localhost:8001` (API)\\n- **Interface_Mount_Selector**: `#root`\\n- **INTEGRATION_TEST_CMD**: `cd ui-gateway && CI=true npx playwright test --reporter=list`\\n## > END_ENVIRONMENT\\n\\n## > BEGIN_MODULE: data-store\\n- **Type**: LEAF\\n- **Description**: PostgreSQL database schema initialization.\\n- **Responsibilities**:\\n  - Create `data-store/init.sql` to define the schema.\\n  - Schema must include tables for storing daily prices, returns, and calculated premiums for the proxy pairs.\\n  - Ensure the schema supports the queries required by `logic-api`.\\n  - No host port mapping; internal Docker network only.\\n  - Data persistence via Docker volumes.\\n## > END_MODULE: data-store\",\n  \"semantic_context\": \"### File: test.py\\n```\\nhello factory\\n```\",\n  \"memory_insights\": \"No historic pgvector insights found for tester.\"\n}\n```\n\nThe SDLC Protocol and your Playbook are your core instructions.\nCRITICAL: If successful, your handoff JSON must strictly validate against this schema:\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"required\": [\n    \"status\",\n    \"phase_completed\",\n    \"module_id\",\n    \"test_files_created\"\n  ],\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"status\": {\n      \"const\": \"success\"\n    },\n    \"phase_completed\": {\n      \"const\": \"TEST_DESIGN\"\n    },\n    \"module_id\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\"\n    },\n    \"test_files_created\": {\n      \"type\": \"array\",\n      \"items\": {\n        \"type\": \"string\"\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\nIf you learn an architecture-critical lesson, permanently save it for your future self using the native `sdlc_store_memory` tool.\n",
        "thought": null,
        "thought_signature": null,
